{{one source|date=October 2018}} {{Infobox protected area | name = Alazani Floodplain Forests Natural Monument | iucn_category = III | photo = Aquila heliaca nest.jpg | photo_caption = [[Tugai]]-type forest in flood-land of Alazani River, SE Georgia. [[Eastern imperial eagle]]'s (''Aquila heliaca'') nest. | map = Georgia#Georgia Kakheti | relief = 1 | map_caption = | location = | nearest_city = [[Dedoplistsqaro]] | coordinates = {{coord|41|41|57|N|46|3|52|E|type:landmark_region:GE-KK_dim:50000|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = | area_acre = | area_km2 =2.04 | area_ref = | authorized = | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | visitation_ref = | governing_body = | website = [http://apa.gov.ge/en/protected-areas/Naturalmonument/abanos-mineraluri-tbis-bunebis-dzegli Alazani Floodplain Forests Natural Monument] }}
'''Alazani Floodplain Forests Natural Monument''' ({{lang-ka|ალაზნის ჭალა}}) is a [[floodplain]] forest located in [[Dedoplistsqaro Municipality]] on banks of [[Alazani River]] in southeastern [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]]. <ref>[https://www.protectedplanet.net/alazani-flood-plane-forests-natural-monument Alazani flood plane forests in Georgia] ''Protected Planet''</ref>
==Location and access== Alazani floodplain forests are located on right bank of [[Alazani River]] to the southwest from village [[:ka:ფიროსმანი (დედოფლისწყაროს მუნიციპალიტეტი)|Pirosmani]], at 165 m above sea level. Protected area covers 204.4 ha of natural floodplain forest. Forest is covered by [[liana]]s and also has in abundance perennial [[walnut]], [[ash]], [[oak]] and [[elm]], as well as characteristic to floodplain forests bushes. Due to density of the forest it takes one hour to make a distance of 1 km on a pedestrian route in [[Kakliskure]] or [[Walnut Bay]].<ref>[https://georgiantravelguide.com/en/routes/kaklis-kure-alanazni-peninsula/ Kaklis Kure - Alanazni peninsula]</ref>
