The '''Sŭngri Refinery''' is a Russian-design oil refinery with a capacity of 2 million tons located in [[Sonbong County|Sŏnbong-gun]], [[Rason Special Economic Zone|Rasŏn Special Economic Zone]], [[North Korea]].<ref>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2013-06-17/mongolia-taps-north-korean-oil-potential-to-ease-russia-reliance</ref> It is served by the [[Sungri Line|Sŭngri Line]] of the [[Korean State Railway]].<ref name="Hayato">Kokubu, Hayato, 将軍様の鉄道  (Shōgun-sama no Tetsudō), p. 93 {{ISBN|978-4-10-303731-6}}</ref> In 2013, a [[Mongolia]]n firm bought a 20% share in the refinery, but sold it off again in 2016.<ref>http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3016554</ref>

