The '''Ulakhan Fault''' is a [[Fault (geology)|left-lateral]] moving [[transform fault]] that runs along the boundary between two [[tectonic]] plates in northeast [[Asia]], the [[North American Plate]], and the [[Okhotsk Plate]]. It runs from a [[triple junction]] in the [[Chersky Range]] in the west, to another triple junction with the [[Aleutian Trench]] and the [[Kuril Trench]] in the east.
